                        <p>
                                <br />
                                <span class="head4">Command: </span>
                                <span class="cmd">xsMergeContexts</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="head4">Category: </span>
                                <span class="bodytext">Conceptual Search</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="head4">Description: </span>
                                <span class="bodytext">Merges two contexts into a new context.  The contexts
                                must have the same number and name of concepts and be of the same context type.
                                The merge occurs in a weighted fashion, meaning the number of events that
                                contributed to each context is taken into account when deciding how to 
                                create the new context.  If the context type is 'average_centered', the avg
                                and stdev are weighted.  If the context type is 'domain', the min and max
                                are weighted.  If the context type is 'median_centered', the median and stdev
                                are weighted.  If the weight of both contexts are 0, then they are of equal 
                                weight and the new context count is set to 0.  If only one context is set to 0,
                                the contexts will be of equal weight and the new context count will be set to 0.
                                </span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="head4">Syntax: </span>
                                <span class="bodytext">xsMergeContexts contextA [in scopeA] and
                                        contextB [in scopeB] into contextC [in scopeC]</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <br />
                                <span class="head4">Example: </span>
                                <span class="code">| xsMergeContexts lastWeekTxn AND thisWeekTxn INTO
                                        weeklyTxn in app</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="explanation">Merges the lastWeekTxn context and thisweekTxn
                                        context into weeklyTxn in the current app</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="head4">Parameters: </span>
                                <span class="bodytext">contextA, contextB, contextC, scopeA, scopeB, scopeC</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="para">contextA</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="explanation">The name of the first Context to merge.</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="para">contextB</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="explanation">The name of the second Context to merge.</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="para">contextC</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="explanation">The name of the merged Context.</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="para">scopeA</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="explanation">The scope of the first Context 
                                (default is search the private/app/global scope)</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="para">scopeB</span>
                        </p><p>
                                <span class="explanation">The scope of the second Context
                                (default is search the private/app/global scope).</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="para">scopeC</span>
                        </p><p>
                                <span class="explanation">The scope of the merged Context
                                (default is private).</span>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <span class="head4">Result: </span>
                                <span class="bodytext">The context is merged. See <a
                                      href="xsUpdateContext">xsUpdateContext</a> for
                                      details about updating a context. </span>
                        </p>
